CN assignment 310-21 was proceeding Eastward on the south track at about 50 mph when it struck the trailer portion of a semi-trailer that was stopped on the crossing. The impact  shoved  the trailer into a SUV wedging the SUV under the semi trailer.  The crossing was a public crossing equipped with FLB&G, mile 95.92 CP Cascade Sub. Emergency services responded. Lone occupant of vehicle sustained fatal injuries. At this location, there is insufficient approach on the north side off Lougheed Highway for a semi-trailer to clear the highway without entering the crossing. There is no pull out lane so a vehicle can pull off the highway without blocking the eastbound lane. The road approach also turns sharply to the east on the south side to parallel the track on the north and the Fraser River on the south. The accident occurred when the southbound semi encountered a northbound SUV on the corner to the south of the crossing, and neither vehicle could continue forward. At that moment, the approaching train activated the signals bringing the gates down on the semi trailer. The SUV occupant's view of the approaching train was obstructed by the trailer.

2304-26 was proceeding eastbound on the north track while en route to North Bend from Port Coquitlam when
they encountered a black sedan car that was foul of the track on the south side at M. 78.3 Cascade Subdivision.
The crew was traveling at track speed, which is 45 MPH at this location, when they noticed headlights as they
were approaching the bend at M. 78.3. The locomotive engineer was under the impression that the lights were
from a hi-rail on the south track and therefore dimmed his lights as they were approaching the vehicle. The
vehicle was struck at 45 MPH and 3 seconds after making contact with the vehicle, the locomotive engineer
made an emergency application and came to a stop 1406 ft. after the emergency application was made. It is
presumed by the police that the car had traveled in between the north and the south main tracks from Nicomen
(M.77) to the point of contact at M. 78.3. No crew members were injured, nor did they seek medical attention
and they declined EFAP.

CN Trainmaster reports having found a white pickup truck at the Conrich School crossing (Mile 117.84, Three Hills Sub.) that appears to have struck a train. The vehicle had been proceeding eastward. Belt-pack assignment operating with CN 7077, CN 1438, CN 7078 and CN 7530 and handling 11L, 75E, 5500T, 6800F, was the last movement over the crossing operating northward. Inspection of the transfer movement indicates that the vehicle struck the movement between line 58, car TTGX 940985 and Line 59, car TTGX 995493, both empty auto carriers with minor damage reported to the side ladders of each car. The crew were unaware that they had been struck at the time of the incident. No injuries reported and no dangerous goods involved. The driver fled the scene. RCMP attended to the scene and the incident remains under investigation.

This has been confirmed as a second train event. There has been recent changes to the crossing configuration. In this area, track is provincially owned, and therefore track is not subject to Railway Safety Act enforcement. TSB does not have jurisdiction over GO Transit owned track.

CP train 100-11 proceeding east on the Brooks Sub., struck the trailer portion of a tractor trailer at public crossing equipped with SRCS at Mile 43.57. Two occupants of the vehicle sustained minor injuries.

CP train 118-26 reports striking an unoccupied vehicle at public crossing (Hwy 26) equipped with FLB&G at Mile 67.24 Mactier Sub. No injuries.

CN train L51851-22 traveling West (long nose leading) with CN 2440 and 4 cars (two loaded grain and two empty grain cars) struck vehicle at public crossing equipped with SRCS, mile 4.48 Alliance Spur. No injuries. No damage to locomotive.

The driver of a pick-up truck reported that the vehicle had struck a CP train at mile 38.61 of the Wilkie Sub in Perdue, SK. Pick-up was found in ditch on fire and serious damage had been done to the signal bungalow. No reported injuries. No DG. Train involved is undetermined at time of posting.
CN train M31651-13 operating on the Rivers Sub struck an automobile at mile 3.89  FLB&G crossing in Waverly St. CN crews responded. No injuries. No derailment.

CP train 467-10 with locomotive CP 9647 struck a Dodge Caliber at rural crossing with crossbucks and stop signs at mile 82.19 of the Red Deer Sub in Penhold, AB. Lone occupant was uninjured. No derailment. No DG.

CP train 674-678 at Yorkton, SK struck a tractor trailer at FLB public crossing mile 25.29 (Yellowhead Hwy #9) of the Wynyard Sub. Minor damage to lead locomotive CP 8758. No derailment. No injuries. No DG.

CN advises receiving report from RCMP that a woman claimed she struck a train at public crossing equipped with FL&B at Mile 34.07, Grande Prairie Sub. No injuries. Last train through was CN A45951-13. Train inspected and no evidence of collision found.

GO train heading west (cab car 1st) on CP's Galt Sub struck an SUV at public crossing equipped with FLB&G,  Erindale Station Rd, mile 17.35. EMS, Police and GO officials responded  Lone occupant of SUV sustained minor injuries and taken to local hospital for further assessment. No derailment. No DG's involved.

CN reports automobile driving around another that was stopped at public crossing, Mile .37 Cargill Lead, equipped with FL&B and striking the 2nd last car (GACX 6745 -load of grain) of train L56041-05 at Dufault SK. No injuries. No derailment.

CN train A40611-05 was proceeding westward on the Sussex Sub when it struck a farm vehicle at a public crossing equipped with FL&B at mile 47.81. CN Police and other CN officials responded. No injuries and only minor damage to the vehicle.

CN L5541-03 was proceeding west on track RS54 of the Rivers Sub when it was struck by a vehicle at a public passive railway crossing. Empty freight cars INTX 43105 and KLEX 1072 sustained damage but did not derail. The lone occupant of the vehicle fled the scene on foot. EMS and CN officials responded. There were no crew injuries and no DG involved.

CN train L57951-03, proceeding on the Dawson Creek Sub., was struck by a truck with trailer as it lost control approaching private farm crossing, Mile 39.56,  and slid into the ditch resulting in the trailer striking the lead locomotive (BCOL 4603) and second unit CN 2410. No injuries. Both units sustained damage.

CN reports C-Tower Hump assignment, locomotive CN 6009, struck employee vehicle at private crossing located in Symington Yard (track CO25). No injuries. No damage to locomotive. CN officials responded.

CN train A41251-29, operating on the Vegreville Sub., was struck by a pick-up truck heading west at public crossing equipped with SRCS + Stop signs. Train was stopped at moment of impact. EMS and CN officials responded. Lone male occupant was taken to local hospital with non-life threatening injuries.

CN freight A-402-51-30, while proceeding eastward on the Watrous subdivision, struck a tractor trailer stalled on a public crossing at mile 197.85 equipped with SRCS. No injuries reported. Local police and CN officials responded.

While proceeding at 24 MPH on the Windsor subdivision, CP freight 240-23 struck a vehicle on St-George street public crossing equipped with flashing light signals and bell. No injuries reported. Local police and CP officials responded.
CP reports train 853-031, proceeding north on the Weyburn Sub., struck a vehicle at public crossing equipped with SRCS at Mile 157.82. No injuries.

While proceeding on Metrolinx's Guelph subdivision, Goderich-Exeter Railway assignment, operating light engines, stuck a vehicle on King Street public crossing equipped with flashing light signals, bell and gates. No injuries reported. Local police and GEXR officials responded.
CP train 387-906 struck a vehicle at public crossing equipped with SRCS at Mile 83.03 Taber Sub. EMS responded and took lone male occupant, with minor injuries, to local hospital for observation.
CP train 387-026, proceeding west on the Crowsnest Sub., struck a utility trailer pulled by a pick-up truck at public crossing equipped with SRCS at Mile 81.93. No injuries. Damage to trailer only.
CN train L52951-27, proceeding on the Grande Prairie Sub., struck a vehicle that was stalled on public crossing equipped with FL&B at Mile 48.78. No injuries.

While proceeding west on the St-Maurice Sub., VIA passenger train 603 struck a northbound pick-up truck at private (Kruger) crossing equipped with SRCS and stop sign at Mile 120.18. The four occupants of the vehicle (same family) sustained varying degrees of injuries. One fatal (adult vehicle passenger), two serious injuries (adult driver and adolescent passenger) and one minor injury (adolescent vehicle passenger). Emergency Response was delayed due to remote location. No injuries to train crew or train passengers. TSB investigators from Montreal and Ottawa responding.

While proceeding west on the St-Maurice Sub., VIA passenger train 603 struck a northbound pick-up truck at private (Kruger) crossing equipped with SRCS and stop sign at Mile 120.18. The four occupants of the vehicle (same family) sustained varying degrees of injuries. One fatal (adult vehicle passenger), two serious injuries (adult driver and adolescent passenger) and one minor injury (adolescent vehicle passenger). Emergency Response was delayed due to remote location. No injuries to train crew or train passengers. TSB investigators from Montreal and Ottawa responding.

While proceeding west on the St-Maurice Sub., VIA passenger train 603 struck a northbound pick-up truck at private (Kruger) crossing equipped with SRCS and stop sign at Mile 120.18. The four occupants of the vehicle (same family) sustained varying degrees of injuries. One fatal (adult vehicle passenger), two serious injuries (adult driver and adolescent passenger) and one minor injury (adolescent vehicle passenger). Emergency Response was delayed due to remote location. No injuries to train crew or train passengers. TSB investigators from Montreal and Ottawa responding.

CP crew on assignment K03-27, shoving 13 empty flat cars into track D5702 to spot customer, had lead car CP 521782 come into contact with a front end loader which moved over customer crossing as movement approached. No injuries. No damage to rail equipment.

While proceeding west on the Drummondville Sub., CN train A40121-13 struck a vehicle at public crossing equipped with FLB&G at Mile 109.10. It was reported that vehicle had rolled into the path of the train (after being stopped). Lone occupant was fatally injured. CN Police, CN Officials and local Emergency Services responded. Four freight trains and four VIA trains were impacted until site released by the Coroner.

CP train 402-08, proceeding north on the Red Deer Sub., was struck by a second vehicle attempting to go around the gates at public crossing located at Mile 47.66. Vehicle struck side of locomotive (fuel tank) which sustained superficial damage. The lone occupant of the vehicle sustained undetermined minor injuries. Local Emergency Services responded.
CN reports train J67351-03, traveling at 48 MPH on the Yale Sub., struck and fatally injured a pedestrian at Public Crossing equipped with FLB&G at Mile 73.05. EMS responded.
CP train 640-046, proceeding east on the Galt Sub, reports striking an abandoned and unattached vehicle trailer left foul of public crossing equipped with SRCS at Mile 92.22. No injuries.

CP train 463-22, proceeding west on the Crowsnest Sub., was struck by a vehicle (at 2nd locomotive) traveling north over public crossing equipped with FL&B at Mile 30.72. Two occupants in vehicle. No injuries.
CP train K09-29, proceeding south on the Weyburn Sub., struck a truck that did not stop as it traveled west over public crossing equipped with SRCS at Mile 102.12. No injuries reported.
CP reports train 293-05 (lead unit CP 9628), proceeding north on the Leduc Sub., struck a vehicle traveling east over public crossing equipped with FLB&G at Mile 35.06. No injuries reported.

RCMP and CN report train Q19851-03, proceeding east on the Sprague Sub. struck an automobile that had crossed the tracks, made a U-turn and crossed (again) the public crossing equipped with SRCS and Stop signs at Mile 114.77. EMS responded. Lone female occupant was flown, by STARS Ambulance, to hospital with serious injuries. No injuries to crew. Minor damage to front of lead locomotive, CN 8895.

CP train 119-29, proceeding west on the Belleville Sub., when an automobile struck the 97th car (CP 527357 - load of non-DG container) at public crossing equipped with FL&B at Mile 60.91. No injuries reported.

CP train 2/244-21, proceeding east on Windsor Sub., struck an automobile at public crossing equipped with SRCS at Mile 90.80. Car spun around and punctured locomotive fuel tank resulting in approx. 250 gallons of spilled diesel fuel. EMS and Hazmat responded.

While shoving 6 loads with employee riding the point, CP assignment N71-18 struck a minivan at public crossing equipped with FL&B at Mile 104.53. Warning devices were operating as intended. Minor injuries to female operator and 2 children in vehicle. Minor damage to step ladder of rail car PROX 74387 (load of asphalt).
CP train TEC-64, proceeding north on Weyburn Sub., struck a tractor-trailer stopped foul of the main track at public crossing equipped with SRCS at Mile 83.25. No injuries reported.
CP train 374-005, proceeding east on the Crowsnest Sub., struck a southbound Tractor-trailer at public crossing equipped with SRCS at Mile 14.81. No injuries to operator or crew.

CP assignment A32-10 proceeding east on Lacombe Sub., struck a farm tractor at public crossing equipped with SRCS at Mile 98.34. Vehicle operator sustained minor injuries and was transported to local hospital for observation. Emergency Services and CP officials responded.

CN reports contract workers from A&B Railway traveling on CN Grande Prairie Sub in a Mark IV Tamper as it was struck by an automobile at Public Crossing equipped with FL&B at Mile 44.16. No injuries to occupant of automobile or crew. Damage was sustained to Mark IV Tamper.

CP reports GO train 160 on Track #1 Main departing Erindale Station on the Galt Sub.,  struck a school bus stopped under the public crossing gate at Mile 17.35. No injuries. Six children and one adult (driver) on the bus. Minor damage to vehicle. Toronto TSB investigators deployed.

CP train 414-19 proceeding east on Minnedosa Sub., struck a northbound pick-up truck at public crossing equipped with SRCS at Mile 43.89. Minor injuries to lone female occupant. EMS and CP officials responded. Vehicle operator was transported to hospital for further assessment.
CN train L55050-21 proceeding north on the Camrose Sub., struck empty cattle trailer traveling east at public crossing equipped with SRCS at Mile 87.01. No injuries. Emergency Services responded.

CN train L56331-20, proceeding east on the Stamford Sub., struck an all terrain vehicle at public crossing equipped with SRCS at Mile 14.17 (Sherk Rd). Lone male occupant  sustained minor injuries to ear and taken to hospital. No injuries to crew. No train or track damage. Emergency Services responding.

While traveling west on the North Track of the CP Vaudreuil Sub., train AMT 27 struck an abandoned vehicle at 3rd Avenue Terrasse-Vaudreuil public crossing equipped with FLB&G at Mile 18.07. Occupant exited vehicle prior to impact. No injuries. No derailment. Emergency Services responded.

CP train 142-05, proceeding east on the Belleville Sub., was struck by a vehicle that was stopped on the south side of the crossing and then appeared to accelerate. The vehicle struck the side of unit CP 8534 sustaining damage to the footboard. Single occupant did not appear to sustain any injuries as they were observed walking around the scene. EMS and CP officials responded.

CP train 101-03, proceeding west on the Cartier Sub., struck and fatally injured a male pedestrian who had stepped in front of the train at public crossing equipped with FLB&G at Mile 90.94 (Main St. E). Emergency Services responded.
CP train 293-28, proceeding east on the Scotford Sub., struck a vehicle at public crossing equipped with FL&B at Mile 172.03 (88th Street). No injuries

CN train Q10721-03 proceeding west on the Redditt Sub., was struck by a vehicle traveling south on public crossing equipped with SRCS and Stop signs at Mile 228.29. Rail car TTRX 370478 sustained minor damage. Vehicle occupants fled the scene on arrival. Emergency Services responded.

CN 2300 belt pack assignment, handling 24 cars eastward out of Customer track (KN21) over public crossing equipped with SRCS at Mile .51 (3.4 Ashcroft Sub.) when a pick-up truck rolled into the side of the movement. The driver's foot was inadvertently removed from the brake allowing vehicle to roll and collide with cars CGTX 30770, CGTX 30817 and CGTX 311276 (L/C diesel). No injuries. Safety appliances damaged on all three cars. No derailment. No leaks. Emergency Services responded.

CN train L56111-03, proceeding east on the Matane Sub., struck an automobile at public crossing equipped with SRCS at Mile 25.82. EMS responded. One serious and one minor injury to occupants. Both were sent to local hospital. No injuries to train crew.

While proceeding westward on the Alexandria subdivision, VIA passenger train 59 struck a pick up truck on a private crossing at mile 10. As a result of the collision, the lone occupant sustained minor injuries. Local police, ambulance and VIA officials responded.

CP assignment NPGA-804-06, while operating light engine on the St-Boniface lead in Winnipeg, contacted a vehicle on a private crossing at mile 2.10. It was further reported that the driver exited the vehicle prior to impact. Local police and CP officials responded.

CP yard assignment KM-23, while making a reverse movement on the Outlook subdivision, contacted a tractor trailer on a public crossing at mile 4.78 equipped with flashing light signals and bells. As a result of the collision, tank car GATX 209836, residue L/C ammonium nitrate, UN 2426 derailed. No injuries or leakage of product reported. Local police and CP officials responded.

CP assignment K-50-22 was proceeding northward on the Weyburn subdivision when it struck a tractor trailer on Avonlea turnoff public crossing equipped with SRCS. As a result of the collision, lead locomotive CP 8738 sustained significant damage. No injuries reported. Local police and CP officials responded.

CP freight 673-008 was struck by a vehicle on Range Road 282 public crossing equipped with SRCS while proceeding westward on the Crowsnest subdivision. As a result of the collision, the driver and a passenger sustained minor injuries. Local police, ambulance and CP officials responded.

CP freight 387-104 was proceeding westward on the Crowsnest subdivision when they were struck by a vehicle on 133 street public crossing equipped with flashing light signals and bell. As a result of the collision, the lone occupant in the vehicle sustained minor injuries and 4 hopper cars were damaged. Local police, ambulance and CP officials responded.

While proceeding on the Albreda subdivision, CN freight Q-196-51-19 struck a tractor trailer on a crossing at mile 70.35. It was further reported that the 2 occupants exited the vehicle prior to the collision. No injuries reported. Local police and CN officials responded.

While proceeding eastward on the Watrous subdivision, CN freight Q-112-52-16 struck a vehicle on 6th Street N.W. public crossing equipped with SRCS. As a result of the collision 1 person sustained serous injuries and was transported to hospital. Local police, ambulance and CN officials responded.

CP train 608-740 proceeding east on the Belleville Sub., struck a stalled automobile (heading north) on public crossing equipped with SRCS at Mile 17.94. Vehicle operator was attempting to push the vehicle clear at time of impact. No injuries. Minor damage to locomotive pilot. Emergency Services responded.

While proceeding north on the Lac St-Jean Sub, CN train L55621-12 struck a camping trailer being pulled by a pick-up truck at public crossing equipped with FL&B at Mile 159,49. Automatic warning device was working properly. No injuries. Minor damage to lead locomotive.

CP train 490-06, proceeding south on the Emerson Sub., was struck by a semi-truck (4th car behind locomotives)at public crossing equipped with FL&B at Mile 24.01 . No derailment. Heavy Fog reported in area. Vehicle occupant was taken to local hospital with undetermined injuries.

VIA train 73, proceeding west on the Chatham Sub., struck a vehicle at public crossing equipped with FL&B at Mile 18.51. Vehicle occupant sustained fatal injuries. No injuries to crew or passengers. Emergency Services responded.

CN reports train A40611-03, proceeding east on the Sussex Sub., struck a pick-up truck at public crossing equipped with FL&B at Mile 10.97. Minor injuries to lone male occupant. Emergency Services responded.
RailTerm reports train CN 518, operating on the (GEXR) Guelph Sub., struck a cyclist at public crossing equipped with FLB&G located at Mile 118.77 (Highbury St.). Cyclist sustained minor injuries.

While proceeding eastward on the Alexandria subdivision, VIA passenger train 59 struck and fatally injured a pedestrian on Russell road public crossing equipped with flashing light signals, bell and gates. Local police, coroner and VIA officials responded,

CP yard assignment UE-2729, while proceeding in track X-25 in Thunder Bay yard, struck a vehicle on a public crossing at mile 0.37 equipped with SRCS. No injuries reported. Local emergency services and CP officials responded.
CN train L52441-18, proceeding on the Warman Sub., struck a vehicle that had stopped foul of the public crossing equipped with FL&B at Mile 5.01. No injuries. No damages reported.

While proceeding westward on Sorel Subd, CN freight train L52621-26 struck a tractor trailer at public crossing equipped with FL&B, at Mile 7.45 (rue Metropole). No injuries. some damage to the lateral ladder and handrail was bended on the front loco CN 4719. No derailment. No damage to track.

CN train G84651-01, traveling on Nechako Sub., came into contact with a vehicle that had been involved in a motor vehicle collision near the railway tracks and came to rest foul of the tracks at the public crossing equipped with FL&B at Mile 8.68. The train crew initiated an emergency brake application and had greatly reduced speed prior to collision with vehicle. No injuries. No damage to train.

0700 assignment on Southern Ontario Railway, shoving on the N & NW Spur, struck a dump truck and trailer with  empty car TILX 257018 at private crossing equipped with SRCS and Stop signs at Victoria Ave (near Mile.55). No injuries.

CP train 118-11, proceeding south on the Mactier Sub., struck the rear of an automobile that was operated around the gates at public crossing equipped with FLB&G at Mile 91.43. Vehicle fled scene. No injuries to train crew. No damage reported.

While proceeding east with 35 cars on the Henri-Bourassa Spur (05S), CN assignment Y59221-22 struck the rear end of vehicle at crossing Mile 0,08.  Tractor trailer was traveling south and stopped abruptly and foul of the track account of stopped traffic. Train initiated an emergency brake application while traveling 3 MPH. No injury. No track damage. No damage to vehicle.

CP coal train 869-072, operating west on CN Yale Sub., struck a vehicle at private crossing equipped with STOP signs at Mile 101.26. No injuries. Vehicle occupant had exited the vehicle and contacted 911 prior to collision.

While proceeding westward at 92 mph on the South mainline of the Kingston Sub, VIA train 33 (consist: 907-3467-3308-3339) struck and fatally injured a pedestrian at public crossing equipped with FLB&G at Mile 17.52 (Woodland Ave.). The warning system was working properly. There were 119 passengers aboard. Emergency Services, coroner and rail officials responded. TSB Investigator (Dorval) deployed.
CN belt pack assignment YMYS01-13 struck a grader stopped on private crossing in Melville yard. No injuries. Damage to safety appliances to 2nd unit (slug) CN 235.

CP train 293-09, traveling west on the Swift Current Sub., struck a semi-trailer traveling north at public crossing equipped with SRCS and STOP signs at Mile 16.78. Collision resulted in the derailment of the two head-end locomotives and 21 cars (2 lds, 19 etys). Male driver sustained minor injuries and was taken to hospital in Moose Jaw. Both RCMP and CP Police responded.
CN train Q11131-09, proceeding north on the Bala Sub., struck and injured a pedestrian at public crossing equipped with FLB&G at Mile 63.84. Emergency Services responding.

During crew change at Chapleau, CP train 101-06 was blocking the Hwy 101 crossing. A blue 1/2 ton pick-up truck, stopped at the crossing, had the vehicle brakes fail allowing the pick-up to roll into the side of train 101. At that moment, the train began its departure, causing further damage to the front of the vehicle. OPP advised the railway of incident after train had departed Chapleau. CP officials arranged for train to be inspected at Thunder Bay. No injuries. No damage to railway equipment found.

While proceeding Westward on South track of the St-Hyacinthe Subdivision, near Lemoyne at Mile 69.51, VIA Rail train # 15 struck a pedestrian, on bicycle, who went around gates and freight train on North Track. The man refuse any medical treatment. Emergency Services responded.

CN train A40541-04, proceeding west on the Gladstone Sub., struck a farm tractor at public crossing equipped with SRCS located at Mile 2.48. No injuries to crew or lone occupant of tractor. No damage or derailment.

CP train 386-280, proceeding south on the Weyburn Sub, was struck on the conductor's side by a white pick-up truck with two occupants at public crossing equipped with SRCS at Mile 139.91. Minor injuries to occupants. No damage to track or equipment.
VIA Rail train 85, traveling west on the Guelph Sub, struck a vehicle at public crossing equipped with SRCS and STOP sign at Mile 57. Emergency Services responding
CP empty ballast train, 6BAL-16, operating on the Wilkie Sub, struck a north bound vehicle at public crossing equipped with lights and bell at Mile 3.37. Lone female occupant was taken to hospital.

CN train Q10251-12, proceeding east on the Blackfoot Sub., struck a vehicle with lone occupant at public crossing equipped with SRCS at Mile 46.85. No injuries. Local emergency services and CN police responded.

CN freight A-443-51-28 struck a vehicle on a public crossing at mile 50.07 of the Three Hills subdivision, equipped with SRCS. It was further reported that the vehicle fled the scene following the collision. Local police and CN officials responded.

While proceeding southward on the Red Deer subdivision, CP freight 351-478 struck a hi-rail track unit speed swing that was operating over the Range Road 362 public crossing equipped with flashing light signals and bell. VIA passenger train 84, while proceeding eastward at 50 MPH on CN's Halton subdivision, struck and fatally injured a pedestrian on Winston Churchill Road public crossing equipped with flashing light signals, bell and gates. Local police, coroner and VIA/CN officials responded.

CN freight L-559-11-21 (operating light engines), while proceeding westward on the Mont-Joli subdivision at 40 MPH, struck a vehicle on Chemin de la Station public crossing equipped with flashing light signals and bell. As a result of the collision, the lone occupant in the vehicle sustained fatal injuries. Local police, coroner and CN officials responded.

CN train L55751-19, proceeding west on the Coronado Sub., struck a vehicle at public crossing equipped with FL&B at Mile 0.64. Lone male occupant sustained minor injuries. No injuries to crew. No damage reported to the train or track.

CN train Q19851-12 struck vehicle at public crossing Mile 122.52 Fraser Sub (Giscome, BC). Three occupants of the vehicle fled the scene. No derailment. No known injuries. Damage to grab irons on CN 2645.
CN train X34791-29, proceeding west on the Sprague Sub., struck an unoccupied vehicle stopped on the tracks at Mile 105.99. No injuries. No derailment.

CN train L51651-11, operating east on the Sangudo Sub. with 57 cars, struck a vehicle at public crossing equipped with SRCS at Mile 82.19. Lone female occupant sustained minor injuries. No injuries to crew. No damage to rail equipment. EMS responding.

While proceeding Eastward on the Drummondville subdivision and as it proceeded over Brock street public crossing, equipped with FLB&G, at Mile 98.17, CN Freight train M30831-07 hit and fatally injured an individual on a bicycle. It was reported by the Surete du Quebec that the cyclist was standing between the gate and the train. The CN train   Crew was unaware of incident. Train inspected and no evidence found. EMS and Local authorities responded.
CN train L54651-05, proceeding north on the Squamish Sub., struck a vehicle  at public crossing equipped with FL&B at Mile 3.72. No injuries. Emergency Services and Police responding.

CP train 298-04, handling 79 cars and operating east on the Wynyard Sub., struck a semi trailer traveling south on public crossing, equipped with SRCS, at Mile 87.05. No injuries to crew or lone occupant. Lead locomotive and 22 cars derailed. Cars included 1 potash load and 9 ballast empties (not upright), 12 ballast empties and locomotive (upright). CP officials responding. Winnipeg TSB investigator deployed.

CP train 673-084, handling 130 loads on the Lanigan Sub., struck a vehicle at public crossing equipped with SRCS at Mile 9.6. No injuries reported. Lone occupant was taken to hospital as precautionary measure. EMS and local authorities responded.
CN train A42231-02, proceeding east on the Stamford Sub., struck a vehicle being towed by a tow truck at public crossing equipped with FL&B at Mile 31.31. No injuries and no damage reported.

CN train A40541-29, proceeding west on Aberdeen Sub., struck a vehicle at public crossing equipped with SRCS at Mile 41.45 (Vonda, SK.). While traveling eastward on the CN Drummondville Sub., VIA train 20 struck a vehicle at public crossing equipped with FLB&G at Mile 117.22. Two vehicle occupants sustained fatal injuries. VIA Rail train 75, proceeding 80 MPH west on the CN Strathroy Sub., struck a farm tractor at private crossing located at Mile 5.2. No injuries. No damage to train.

CN reports being advised by Miramichi police that a truck had struck train W91211-25 at public crossing equipped with FL&B at Mile 3.69 (Nelson Street) Loggieville spur. Crew was unaware of contact. CN train A45131-23, proceeding north on the Newmarket Sub., struck a vehicle stopped foul of public crossing equipped with FL&B at Mile 104.50 (Sparrow Lake Rd.). Lone occupant of vehicle was uninjured. No injuries to crew. CN officials and local authorities responding.

CP train crew on L34-14, handling 163 empties, witnessed a semi-truck swerve to avoid their train and rollover in the ditch at Mile 55 (Sylvite) Rocanville Sub. Crew stopped to inspect.  Inspection revealed truck paint on fuel tank and step of 2nd unit CP 8908. No injuries reported.

CN train L54641-12, proceeding east on the Rivers Sub., struck and fatally injured adult male pedestrian standing on the crossing equipped with FLB&G at Mile 8.26 (Fairmont Road). No injuries to crew. Local EMS and CN officials responding.

CN train Q10651-08, operating on CP Page Sub, struck a vehicle at the 216th street public crossing equipped with FLB&G at Mile 18.81. Driver of vehicle critically injured and transported by air to hospital. No injuries to crew. No damages to train. Local EMS responding.

CP train 469-25 proceeding south on the Aldersyde Sub. with 120 cars, struck an automobile traveling east at public crossing equipped with SRCS at Mile 7.34. Lone occupant sustained fatal injuries. No injuries to crew.
CN train L52951-24 was struck by a vehicle that collided with trailing locomotive, CN 2615 at public crossing equipped with SRCS at Mile 40.92 Grande Prairie Sub. No injuries to crew or occupants.

CN train Q11131-30 proceeding west on the Wainwright Sub., struck a semi-trailer at public crossing equipped with SRCS at Mile 26.43. No injuries. No derailment. No leaks. EMS and CN police responding.
CN train L59632-15, proceeding east on the Bala Sub., struck a sidewalk plow at public crossing (Young Street) equipped with FL&B at Mile 275.63. No injuries or damages reported.

CP train 387-474, proceeding north on the Emerson Sub., was struck by a vehicle traveling east at public crossing equipped with FL&B at Mile 4.35 (Beaverhill Blvd.). CN Train 41651-10 traveling east on the Yale Sub, struck a Waste Management truck at public crossing equipped with SRCS at Mile 101.7. Driver, with undetermined injuries, taken to hospital by air ambulance. EMS and local authorities responded.

CN train A41251-28, proceeding east on the Blackfoot Sub., was struck by a vehicle at public crossing equipped with SRCS and STOP signs at Mile 89.58. Vehicle struck lead locomotive CN 5362. No injuries. CN officials and local emergency services responded.

CN train L42141-28, proceeding north on the Yorkton Sub., struck a pedestrian walking north on ROW, at public crossing, equipped with FL&B, at Mile 24.74. Pedestrian sustained undetermined injuries. CN officials and local emergency services responded.

CN train C76751-27 proceeding west on the Foothills Sub., was struck by a semi-tractor trailer at public crossing equipped with SRCS at Mile 11.1. No injuries. No derailment. CP train 389-672, proceeding west on the Crowsnest Sub., struck a vehicle at public crossing equipped with SRCS at Mile 15.86 (Monarch). Vehicle fled the scene. No injuries to crew. No damage to track. Minor damage to unit UP 5545. CP officials responded.

CN train Q11451-23, traveling north on the Three Hills Sub., struck a vehicle at 68th Street public crossing equipped with FL&B at Mile 122.13. CP assignment 7WKA-19 proceeding east with light engines on the Kaministiquia Sub., struck a vehicle with two occupants as they approached public crossing, equipped with SRCS, at Mile 59.2. No injuries. CP officials and railway police responded.

CP train 868-906 traveling east on the Shuswap Sub., contacted a vehicle on the ROW at Mile 39. Lone occupant transported to hospital with undetermined injuries. CP officials and local emergency services responded.

CP reports train 460-08 traveling east on the Swift Current Sub., struck a tractor trailer at public crossing equipped with SRCS at Mile 29.0. Collision resulted in the derailment of both locomotives and 9 cars (various DG's - all upright). No injuries. CP officials responding. Two TSB investigators from Toronto Regional Office are deployed.

CP train 675-055, proceeding west on the Wynyard Sub, was struck by a vehicle at public crossing equipped with FLB&G at Mile 28.84. Crew was unaware of incident and was advised to stop and inspect their train by the RTC. Inspection revealed damage to "A" end ladder on 79th car CITX 151907 (load of potash). CN train M31441-02 reports striking a vehicle at public crossing equipped with SRCS Mile 112.5 Bala Sub. Occupants were not in the vehicle at the time of collision. No injuries. No damage to equipment. CN and local authorities responding.

CN 1100 beltpack assignment, traveling west on LuLu Island Industrial Spur, was struck by a vehicle (Waste Management Truck) on private crossing (D074 - access road to Richply). No injuries reported. CN officials and local authorities responding.
CN 2200 Fort St. John yard assignment struck a vehicle at farm crossing located at Mile 718.17, Fort St. John Sub. Vehicle was unoccupied at time of impact. No injuries. CN officials responding.

While pushing a cut of 5 cars, CN 7017 stuck a vehicle at public crossing Mile .27 Port Spur (rue Riverside) equipped with FL&B. No injuries. No track or equipment damage. CN officials and local authorities responded.

CP CWR train aWMO-18, making a reverse movement on the Taber subdivision, struck a tractor trailer on a private crossing at mile 64.0. No injuries reported. Local police and CP officials responded.

SOUTHERN ONTARIO RAILWAY OFFICIALS (SOR) REPORTED A VEHICLE STRUCK THE REAR PORTION OF TRAIN SOR 597-15 (BRANTFORD TURN) ON STANLEY AVENUE PUBLIC CROSSING EQUIPPED WITH FLASHING LIGHT SIGNALS AND BELL. AS A RESULT OF THE COLLISION THE VEHICLE WAS WEDGED UNDER A TANK CAR AND WAS DRAGGED UNTIL IT STRUCK A BRIDGE AT WHICH TIME THE VEHICLE EXPLODED INTO FLAMES. SOR OFFICIALS RESPONDED. TSB (TORONTO) INVESTIGATOR DEPLOYED.
